Direct Known Subclasses:
AlpSocietySet, ExtSocietySet
public abstract class AgentSocietySet
extends java.util.HashSet

An AgentSocietySet is an abstract class used to collect Liaison agent references, either ALPAgentReferences or ExternalAgentReferences. This class also defines all of the methods used for navigating the implied tree structure for the society.

1.0

getChildren

public java.util.ArrayList getChildren(AgentReference parent)
This method returns an ArrayList containing the children of a parent note sorted in alphabetical order. -- in the future this may need to support multiple types of ordering. This method could be modified to take a comparator as an additional argument.

getDescendants

public java.util.ArrayList getDescendants(AgentReference parent)
Return an ArrayList containing ALL descendents of a parent This list is not sorted. The parent is NOT included! Note-- this algorithm will not need to be modified when non-atomic neighborhoods are introduced.

getAgentByName

public AgentReference getAgentByName(java.lang.String agentName)

getParent

public AgentReference getParent(AgentReference child)
Returns the parent of the specifed agent, or null if the specified agent is the root node. Currently, this implementation assumes no heirarchical subdivisions of neighborhoods.

getAncestors

public java.util.ArrayList getAncestors(AgentReference child)
Return an ArrayList of all ancestors for a specified node. The ordering of the list goes from the closest ancestor to the top of the tree. This routine has NO dependencies on how neighborhoods are treated.
